    ðŸ”¹ `diff -i file1 file2` --> Ignores case differences (upper/lowercase).
    ðŸ”¹ `diff -w file1 file2` --> Ignores whitespace differences, such as extra spaces or tabs.

ðŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ diff file1.txt file2.txt

    ðŸ”¹ Shows the differences between the two files in a standard format.

    $ diff -y file1.txt file2.txt

    ðŸ”¹ Compares the files side by side, making it easier to see the changes.

âœ… **Simple Example:**

